I. What do I expect to be in the key file:
    1. in the .pub file itself, I expect to find the string "ssh-rsa", followed by mpint e and n which forms the key "blob" (page 14 of https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/html/rfc4253). 
        The 2 mpints form a String. Finally, the file will end with the username of the one who generated the key.
    2. The key itself will contain:
        1. 4 bytes of integer describing the length of the string "ssh-rsa"
        2. the string "ssh-rsa"
        3. 4 bytes of integer describing the length of RSA exponent
        4. the RSA exponent
        5. 4 bytes of integer describing the length of RSA modulus
        6. the RSA key modulus

II. Decoding the key.

    Steps taken:
        1. Key in command: cat id_rsa_homework.pub | cut -d " " -f2 | base64 -d | hexdump -ve '/1 "%02x "' -e '2/8 "\n"'
        2. Get the binary representation, and decode.

        00 00 00 03 = 4 bytes of integer describing the length of RSA exponent; translates to 3; at range 10,14
